      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is fundamentally rooted in the idea that the Constitution is a fixed document, not a malleable political statement. Proponents argue that the Founders intended a specific meaning for the text, and judges must adhere to that original public meaning. This approach prevents unelected judges from imposing their personal, ever-changing policy preferences onto the law. Therefore, originalism ensures stability and respects the democratic will as it existed at the time of ratification.",
